 a private equity firm specializing in growth equity management or leveraged buyouts recapitalizations pipes investments and managerled search companies it seeks to invest in turnarounds special situations lower middle market and established and mature businesses but may also evaluate startup opportunities the firm typically invests in companies operating in business and technology communications and healthcare sectors the firm also considers investment in companies operating in the energy media and retail and financial services industries in the business and technology sectors it invests in companies operating in application and niche vertical software business process outsourcers commercial and industries education and training hosted application internet services it services logistics and specialty distribution online marketing physical and network security within communications it focuses on bb mediadatabases cablebroadband communications infrastructuremetro fiber networks datacenterscollocation business information services hosted and cloud services and machine to machine communication and wiredwireless telecommunication within healthcare it focus on behavioral health consumer driven healthcare models end of life care healthcare data analytics and information technology specialty providers wellness healthcare equipment healthcare providers and services specialty pharmaceuticals it invests in north america with an overall focus on the united states the firm seeks to invest between  million and  million in companies with enterprise value between  million and  million and annual revenues between  million and  million the firm typically requires active board participation it prefers to make control investments and take majority or minority stake the firm often provides first time institutional capital the firm invests in companies having high barriers to entry it typically invests for a period between four and seven years although it might be flexible the firm was 